Comparing the export values of Colombia between the years 2011 and 2020, the value in 2020 was "$39.48 billion" and in 2011 was "$40.24 billion". To calculate the percentage change, we subtract the value in 2011 from the value in 2020, divide the result by the 2011 value, and multiply by 100.

Percentage change = [(Value in 2020 - Value in 2011) / Value in 2011] x 100

Percentage change = [($39.48 billion - $40.24 billion) / $40.24 billion] x 100

Percentage change = (-$0.76 billion / $40.24 billion) x 100

Percentage change ≈ -0.0189 x 100

Percentage change ≈ -1.89%

However, since we are rounding to the nearest whole number, the percentage decrease in Colombia's exports from 2011 to 2020 is approximately 1.6%.
